                                <condition key="deficient">
                                    The manuscript is severely damaged, however it still retains the binding and all the leaves without loss of text.
                                    The leaves are stained by water, dirt, droppings, and wax. Losses caused by insects are present.
                                    The border around a loss in the upper margin of <locus target="#36"></locus> is darkened, perhaps burned.
                                    Many tears in the leaves have been repaired by sewing (e.g. <locus target="#26 #28 #29"></locus>)
                                    The back board is divided in two halves by a crack along the vertical axis. The two halves are held together by various
                                    threads passing through pairs of holes drilled in the board.
                                    The portion of leather covering the back is torn and lacks part of the tail. The endbands are missing.
                                    The sewing is broken at the uppermost pair of sewing stations in <ref target="#q6"></ref>.
                                </condition>
