                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true Ethiopian">
                              <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards with a blind-tooled <material
                                key="leather">leather</material> which covers only the spine and the back edge of the boards.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                The boards are flush with the bookblock and have external shallow bevels. The grain runs vertically.
                                The outer surface and the edges of the boards are polished and a layer of dark-coloured finish has been added, while the inner surface exhibits signs of the working tool.
                                The lower board is separated vertically in two halves which are held together with various threads passing through pairs of holes drilled in the board.
                                On the inner surface of the upper board, in the middle, remnants of a grayish substance are present, which perhaps was used to glue a <term key="mirror">mirror</term>.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Cover" color="reddish-brown">
                                The boards and the spine are partially covered with a reddish-brown leather featuring a blind-tooled decoration.
                                On the surface of the boards and on the back, bands of two <term key="singleStraightLine">single straight lines</term> intersect
                                forming two columns of juxtaposed panels. Within each panel, the lines cross each other forming a crux decussata. Within a panel
                                on the lower boards the lines also form a 4-pointed star.
                                The turn-ins and the edges are not decorated. On the inner side of the boards, between the turn-ins, <term key="additionalLeatherPatch">additional leather patches</term>
                                have been added. On the one on the upper board, an angel <!-- is it an angel? -->is drawn in pencil.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Endbands">
                                The endbands are missing.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b6">
                                Chainstitch sewing on four sewing stations (two pairs); periodic fold pattern; Z-plied threads.
                                In the quires, between each pair of sewing stations, there are two lengths of thread.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b7" type="Spine">
                                At the head are preserved the horizontal short stitches used to pierce the leather on the spine in two points (at the head and tail), thus fixing the endbands to the cover.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b8" type="Other">
                                Threads of various colours are inserted in the outer margins for navigating the text.
                                More specifically, a black <term key="leafStringMark">leaf string marker</term> is inserted in <locus target="#28"/> and a
                                purple <term key="leafStringMark">leaf string marker</term> is inserted in <locus target="#113"/>.
                              </decoNote>
                            </binding>
